At the hearing on 18th November 2015 the family respondents sought “early resolution of court proceedings” [A65]. The Local Authority considered that proceedings did not need to continue but the Official Solicitor sought an order to give effect to Ms. Bairstow’s recommendations over a 6 month period, with a further review by the Court. The order [B77

 Made by District Judge Glentworth, the only occasion when judicial continuity was not possible. 
	      ] records all parties’ agreement that a care plan formulated in accordance with Ms Bairstow’s report was in MB’s best interests, and NB’s agreement “not to obstruct or impede the implementation of the care plan” but the Court declined to terminate proceedings. The matter was listed for hearing after 7 months.
